WEBVTT

00:00.780 --> 00:22.560
25. O Lord, thou art my God! I will exalt thee, I will praise thy name, for thou hast done

00:22.560 --> 00:27.700
wonderful things, thy counsels of old are faithfulness and truth, for thou hast made

00:27.700 --> 00:33.960
of a city a heap, of a defenced city a ruin, a palace of strangers to be no city, it shall

00:33.960 --> 00:38.920
never be built. Therefore shall the strong people glorify thee, the city of the terrible

00:38.920 --> 00:43.740
nations shall fear thee, for thou hast been a strength to the poor, a strength to the

00:43.740 --> 00:48.900
needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shadow from the heat, when the blast of

00:48.900 --> 00:54.200
the terrible ones is as a storm against the wall. Thou shalt bring down the noise of strangers,

00:54.200 --> 01:00.060
as the heat in a dry place, even the heat with the shadow of a cloud, the branch of the terrible

01:00.060 --> 01:05.780
ones shall be brought low. And in this mountain shall the Lord of hosts make unto all people a

01:05.780 --> 01:12.100
feast of fat things, a feast of wines on the lees, of fat things full of marrow, of wines on the lees

01:12.100 --> 01:17.540
well refined. And he will destroy in this mountain the face of the covering cast over all people,

01:17.860 --> 01:23.440
and the veil that is spread over all nations. He will swallow up death in victory, and the Lord God

01:23.440 --> 01:28.860
will wipe away tears from off all faces, and the rebuke of his people shall he take away from off

01:28.860 --> 01:34.980
all the earth, for the Lord hath spoken it. And it shall be said in that day, Lo, this is our God,

01:35.240 --> 01:40.260
we have waited for him, and he will save us, this is the Lord, we have waited for him, we will be

01:40.260 --> 01:45.780
glad and rejoice in his salvation. For in this mountain shall the hand of the Lord rest, and Moab

01:45.780 --> 01:51.200
shall be trodden down under him, even as straw is trodden down for the dung hill. And he shall

01:51.200 --> 01:56.100
spread forth his hands in the midst of them, as he that swimmeth spreadeth forth his hands to swim,

01:56.520 --> 02:01.320
and he shall bring down their pride together with the spoils of their hands. And the fortress of the

02:01.320 --> 02:06.800
high fort of thy walls shall he bring down, lay low, and bring to the ground, even to the dust.

02:07.660 --> 02:14.100
Chapter 26. In that day shall this song be sung in the land of Judah. We have a strong city,

02:14.660 --> 02:19.440
salvation will God appoint for the walls and bulwarks. Open ye the gates that the righteous

02:19.440 --> 02:24.000
nation which keepeth the truth may enter in. Thou wilt keep him in perfect peace,

02:24.140 --> 02:28.840
whose mind is stayed on thee, because he trusteth in thee. Trust ye in the Lord forever,

02:29.180 --> 02:34.020
for in the Lord Jehovah is everlasting strength. For he bringeth down them that dwell on high.

02:34.280 --> 02:39.860
The lofty city he layeth it low, he layeth it low even to the ground, he bringeth it even to the dust.

02:40.260 --> 02:44.200
The foot shall tread it down, even the feet of the poor, and the steps of the needy.

02:44.200 --> 02:49.660
The way of the just is uprightness. Thou most upright dost weigh the path of the just.

02:50.540 --> 02:53.580
Yea, in the way of thy judgments, O Lord, we have waited for thee.

02:53.880 --> 02:57.940
The desire of our soul is to thy name, and to the remembrance of thee.

02:58.640 --> 03:03.560
With my soul have I desired thee in the night. Yea, with my spirit within me will I seek thee

03:03.560 --> 03:08.720
early. For when thy judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.

03:09.440 --> 03:13.140
Let favor be showed to the wicked, yet will he not learn righteousness.

03:13.720 --> 03:18.580
In the land of uprightness will he deal unjustly, and will not behold the majesty of the Lord.

03:19.260 --> 03:23.000
Lord, when thy hand is lifted up, they will not see, but they shall see,

03:23.180 --> 03:27.940
and be ashamed for their envy at the people. Yea, the fire of thine enemies shall devour them.

03:28.400 --> 03:33.740
Lord, thou wilt ordain peace for us, for thou also hast wrought all our works in us.

03:33.740 --> 03:40.100
O Lord our God, other Lords beside thee have had dominion over us, but by thee only will we make

03:40.100 --> 03:45.600
mention of thy name. They are dead, they shall not live. They are deceased, they shall not rise.

03:46.060 --> 03:50.360
Therefore hast thou visited and destroyed them, and made all their memory to perish.

03:50.940 --> 03:54.620
Thou hast increased the nation, O Lord. Thou hast increased the nation.

03:55.040 --> 03:59.360
Thou art glorified. Thou hast removed it far unto all the ends of the earth.

03:59.920 --> 04:05.280
Lord, in trouble have they visited thee. They poured out a prayer when thy chastening was

04:05.280 --> 04:10.300
upon them. Like as a woman with child that draweth near the time of her delivery is in pain,

04:10.660 --> 04:16.420
and crieth out in her pangs, so have we been in thy sight, O Lord. We have been with child,

04:16.640 --> 04:22.060
we have been in pain, we have as it were brought forth wind, we have not wrought any deliverance

04:22.060 --> 04:27.100
in the earth, neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen. Thy dead men shall live,

04:27.100 --> 04:32.080
together with my dead body shall they arise. Awake and sing, ye that dwell in the dust,

04:32.340 --> 04:37.660
for thy dew is as the dew of herbs, and the earth shall cast out the dead. Come, my people,

04:38.040 --> 04:42.520
enter thou into thy chambers, and shut thy doors about thee. Hide thyself, as it were,

04:42.540 --> 04:47.800
for a little moment, until the indignation be overpassed. For behold, the Lord cometh out of

04:47.800 --> 04:52.900
his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity. The earth also shall disclose

04:52.900 --> 05:00.380
her blood, and shall no more cover her slain. Chapter 27. In that day the Lord with his saw

05:00.380 --> 05:06.600
and great and strong sword shall punish Leviathan the piercing serpent, even Leviathan that crooked

05:06.600 --> 05:13.080
serpent, and he shall slay the dragon that is in the sea. In that day sing ye unto her a vineyard

05:13.080 --> 05:19.480
of red wine. I the Lord do keep it, I will water it every moment, lest any hurt it I will keep it

05:19.480 --> 05:24.900
night and day. Fury is not in me. Who would set the briers and thorns against me in battle?

05:25.140 --> 05:29.840
I would go through them, I would burn them together. Or let him take hold of my strength,

05:30.060 --> 05:35.380
that he may make peace with me, and he shall make peace with me. He shall cause them that come of

05:35.380 --> 05:40.420
Jacob to take root. Israel shall blossom and bud, and fill the face of the world with fruit.

05:41.120 --> 05:46.320
Hath he smitten him, as he smote those that smote him? Or is he slain according to the

05:46.320 --> 05:50.420
order of them that are slain by him? In measure, when it shooteth forth,

05:50.720 --> 05:56.920
thou wilt debate with it. He stayeth this rough wind in the day of the east wind. By this therefore

05:56.920 --> 06:02.460
shall the iniquity of Jacob be purged, and this is all the fruit to take away his sin. When he

06:02.460 --> 06:07.100
maketh all the stones of the altar as chalk stones that are beaten in the sunder, the groves and

06:07.100 --> 06:13.120
images shall not stand up. Yet the defenced city shall be desolate, and the habitation forsaken and

06:13.120 --> 06:18.300
left like a wilderness. There shall the calf feed, and there shall he lie down and consume the

06:18.300 --> 06:22.920
branches thereof. When the boughs thereof are withered, they shall be broken off. The women

06:22.920 --> 06:28.580
come and set them on fire, for it is a people of no understanding. Therefore he that made them will

06:28.580 --> 06:34.100
not have mercy on them, and he that formed them will show them no favour. And it shall come to

06:34.100 --> 06:38.460
pass in that day, that the Lord shall beat off from the channel of the river unto the stream of

06:38.460 --> 06:44.180
Egypt, and ye shall be gathered one by one, O ye children of Israel. And it shall come to pass

06:44.180 --> 06:48.860
in that day, that the great trumpet shall be blown, and they shall come which were ready to

06:48.860 --> 06:54.080
perish in the land of Assyria and the outcasts in the land of Egypt, and shall worship the Lord

06:54.080 --> 06:59.580
in the holy mount at Jerusalem. End of chapters 25 to 27.

